bilingual.source: He was caught being dishonest during the exam.
bilingual.target: 他在考试中被抓到不诚实的行为。

bilingual.source: A dishonest person might try to cheat you out of your money.
bilingual.target: 一个不诚实的人可能会试图骗取你的钱。

bilingual.source: It's dishonest to lie about your qualifications on a job application.
bilingual.target: 在求职申请中谎报资历是不诚实的。
人们不喜欢不诚实的孩子。

bilingual.source: He who lies and cheats is dishonest.
bilingual.target: 他谁的谎言和欺骗，是不诚实的。

bilingual.source: It is dishonest to lie about ones age.
I don't love dishonest person like him.
bilingual.target: 我不喜欢像他那样不诚实的人
永远不要跟不诚实的人为伴。

yingyinNormal.en: As adults, we are almost never dishonest, and that can be a very good thing.
yingyinNormal.zh: 作为成年人，我们几乎一直很诚实，这当然是很好的事情。
yingyinNormal.videoNameZh: 《Facebook COO谢丽尔·桑德伯格哈佛演讲》

yingyinNormal.en: Seriously, you have got to let me scan your brain when you're being dishonest so I can see what lights up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我是说认真的，你得让我扫描你大脑看看你撒谎时哪些区域会亮起。

yingyinNormal.en: It might actually become easier and easier for people to be dishonest and still think of themselves as being honest.
yingyinNormal.zh: 人们越来越容易在做出不诚信行为的时候，还认为自己是诚信的。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: behaving or prone to behave in an untrustworthy or fraudulent way

examination_example.sentence: A Canadian study found that children as young as 14 months can differentiate between a credible person and a <highlight>dishonest</highlight> one.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 加拿大的一项研究发现，14个月大的孩子就能区分开一个可信的人和一个不诚实的人。

examination_example.sentence: It's not that people's profiles are <highlight>dishonest</highlight>, says Catalina Toma of Wisconsin-Madison University,"but they portray an idealised version of themselves."
examination_example.sentence_trans: 威斯康星-麦迪逊大学的卡特琳娜·托马说，并不是人们的个人形象是不真诚的，“而是他们描绘了一个理想化的自己。”

examination_example.sentence: The fact that this is not an uncommon occurrence means that <highlight>dishonest</highlight> persons might be able to access bank accounts in electronic payments systems.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 事实上，这种情况并不罕见，这意味着图谋不轨的人可能会入侵电子支付系统中的银行账户。
